readme.md

Awesome

     A curated list of small, focused Node.js modules.

   Inspired by the [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome]awesome list
   thing.

Articles

     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/ama/issues/10]One-line node
       modules
     * [http://thenodeway.io/introduction/#build-small-single-purpose-modu
       les]Build small single purpose modules
     * [https://github.com/mattdesl/module-best-practices]Module best
       practices
     * [http://bytearcher.com/articles/evaluating-packages-1-check-communi
       ty/]Evaluating Packages Part 1 - Turn to community
     * [http://bytearcher.com/articles/evaluating-packages-2-review-reposi
       tory/]Evaluating Packages Part 2 - Review repository
     * [https://medium.com/@Rich_Harris/small-modules-it-s-not-quite-that-
       simple-3ca532d65de4]Small modules: it's not quite that simple
     * [http://thefullstack.xyz/hyper-modular-packages-a-crazy-cult-or-a-r
       easonable-practice/]Hyper Modular Packages: A Crazy Cult or a
       Reasonable Practice?
     * [https://medium.freecodecamp.com/in-defense-of-hyper-modular-javasc
       ript-33934c79e113]In Defense of Hyper Modular JavaScript
     * [http://g14n.info/2015/12/tiny-npm-package/]Tiny npm package:
       Guidelines to create a Node.js module following the small package
       philosophy
     * [https://nolanlawson.com/2016/08/15/the-cost-of-small-modules/]The
       cost of small modules
     * [http://codetunnel.io/why-i-think-micro-packages-are-a-good-thing/]
       Why I think "micro-packages" are a good thing.

Modules

Array

     * [https://github.com/dcousens/is-sorted]is-sorted - A small module
       to check if an Array is sorted.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/array-first]array-first - Get the
       first element or first n elements of an array.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/array-last]array-last - Return
       the last element in an array.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/arr-flatten]arr-flatten -
       Recursively flatten an array or arrays.
     * [https://github.com/seriousManual/dedupe]dedupe - Remove duplicates
       from an array.
     * [https://github.com/mattdesl/array-range]array-range - Creates a
       new array with given range.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/arr-diff]arr-diff - Returns an
       array with only the unique values from the first array, by
       excluding all values from additional arrays using strict equality
       for comparisons.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/filled-array]filled-array -
       Returns an array filled with the specified input
     * [https://github.com/parro-it/map-array]map-array - Map object keys
       and values into an array.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/in-array]in-array - Return true
       if any of passed values exists in array - faster than using
       indexOf.
     * [https://github.com/mafintosh/unordered-array-remove]unordered-arra
       y-remove - Efficiently remove an element from an unordered array
       without doing a splice.
     * [https://github.com/michaelzoidl/swap-array]array-swap - Swap
       position of two items in an array.
     * [https://github.com/johnwquarles/mirrarray]mirrarray - Creates a
       keymirror object from an array of valid keys.
     * [https://github.com/doowb/group-array]group-array - Group array of
       objects into lists.
     * [https://github.com/zhiyelee/array.chunk]array.chunk - Split
       array/TypedArray to chunks of given size.

String

     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/decamelize]decamelize - Convert a
       camelized string into a lowercased one with a custom separator:
       unicornRainbow -> unicorn_rainbow.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/pad-left]pad-left - Left pad a
       string with zeros or a specified string.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-camel-case]to-camel-case -
       Convert a string to a camel case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-capital-case]to-capital-case
       - Convert a string to a capital case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-constant-case]to-constant-cas
       e - Convert a string to a constant case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-dot-case]to-dot-case -
       Convert a string to a dot case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-no-case]to-no-case - Remove
       an existing case from a string.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-pascal-case]to-pascal-case -
       Convert a string to a pascal case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-sentence-case]to-sentence-cas
       e - Convert a string to a sentence case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-snake-case]to-snake-case -
       Convert a string to a snake case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-space-case]to-space-case -
       Convert a string to a space case.
     * [https://github.com/ianstormtaylor/to-title-case]to-title-case -
       Convert a string to a title case.
     * [https://github.com/dodo/node-slug]node-slug - slugifies even utf-8
       chars.
     * [https://github.com/sergejmueller/rtrim]rtrim - Strip whitespace -
       or other characters - from the end of a string.
     * [https://github.com/hustcc/slice.js]slice.js - Javascript library
       to engance String.substring / Array.slice with python slice style.
     * [https://github.com/chalk/strip-ansi]strip-ansi - Strip ANSI escape
       codes.
     * [https://github.com/ericnorris/striptags]striptags - An
       implementation of PHP's strip_tags in Node.js.
     * [https://github.com/ErikOnBike/parse-next-json-value]parse-next-jso
       n-value - Parse next JSON value from string allowing extraneous
       characters after value.

Date & Time

     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/pretty-ms]pretty-ms - Convert
       milliseconds to a human readable string: 1337000000 -> 15d 11h 23m
       20s.
     * [https://github.com/seriousManual/hirestime]hirestime - A wrapper
       around the built-in high resolution timer which simplifies the
       calculation of timestamps.
     * [https://github.com/timruffles/periods]periods - Defined
       time-periods constants for Javascript, in milliseconds.
     * [https://github.com/taylorhakes/fecha]fecha - Javascript Date
       formatting and parsing.
     * [https://github.com/jucrouzet/akamai-time-reference]akamai-time-ref
       erence - Get reference time using Akamai's time reference service.
     * [https://github.com/hustcc/timeago.js]timeago.js - A tiny(~1.7kb)
       library used to format date with *** time ago statement.
     * [https://github.com/shinnn/count-days-in-month]count-days-in-month
       - Get the number of days in a given month.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/time-stamp]time-stamp - Get a
       formatted timestamp.
     * [https://github.com/vutran/twas]twas - Generate a relative time
       string (Example: "3 seconds ago")

Object

     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/map-obj]map-obj - Map object keys
       and values into a new object.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/filter-obj]filter-obj - Filter
       object keys and values into a new object.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/object-values]object-values - Get
       the values of an object.
     * [https://github.com/eush77/object-pairs]object-pairs - Turn an
       object into list of [key, value] pairs for mapping, iterating or
       other purposes.
     * [https://github.com/landau/zipmap]zipmap - Returns a map with the
       keys mapped to the corresponding vals. zipmap also accepts a single
       value of objects or pairs.
     * [https://github.com/jarofghosts/just-pluck]just-pluck - Pluck
       without the madness.
     * [https://github.com/substack/node-deep-equal]deep-equal - Node's
       assert.deepEqual() algorithm as a standalone module.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/deep-assign]deep-assign -
       Recursive Object.assign().
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/set-value]set-value - Create
       nested values and any intermediaries dot notation ('a.b.c') paths.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/get-value]get-value - Use
       property paths (a.b.c) to get a nested value from an object.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/has-value]has-value - Returns
       true if a value exists, false if empty. Works with deeply nested
       values using dot notation ('a.b.c') paths.
     * [https://github.com/ryanaghdam/has-key-deep]has-key-deep -
       Deep-search objects for keys. Keys can be searched by providing an
       array of keys, or using a dot-notiation.
     * [https://github.com/ricardobeat/flatkeys]flatkeys - Flatten object
       key hierarchies into a list of strings using a custom separator.
     * [https://github.com/watson/flatten-obj]flatten-obj - Converts an
       object literal with deeply nested nodes to a simple key/value
       object.
     * [https://github.com/gummesson/is-empty-object]is-empty-object -
       Check if an object is empty.
     * [https://github.com/yeoman/stringify-object]stringify-object -
       Stringify an object/array like JSON.stringify just without all the
       double-quotes.
     * [https://github.com/domenic/sorted-object]sorted-object - Returns a
       copy of an object with its keys sorted.
     * [https://github.com/fibo/static-props]static-props - Defines static
       object attributes using Object.defineProperties
     * [https://github.com/vladgolubev/missing-deep-keys]missing-deep-keys
       - Returns an array of keys from first object that are missing in
       second.
     * [https://github.com/LinusU/has-own-property]has-own-property -
       Check if an object has a local property.
     * [https://github.com/shevaroller/node-merge-objects]merge-objects -
       Deep-merge two objects. Arrays that are values of the same object
       key get concatenated.
     * [https://github.com/mattphillips/deep-object-diff]deep-object-diff
       - Deep diff two JavaScript Objects while preserving the data
       structure. Including nested structures of Arrays and Objects.

Function

     * [https://github.com/stoeffel/compose-function]compose-function -
       Compose a new function from smaller functions f(g(x)).
     * [https://github.com/dominictarr/curry]curry - A curry function
       without anything too clever.
     * [https://github.com/isaacs/once]once - Run a function exactly one
       time.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/deep-bind]deep-bind - Bind a
       context to all functions in an object, including deeply nested
       functions.
     * [https://github.com/substack/identity-function]identity-function -
       Always return the input argument.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/mem]mem - An optimization
       technique used to speed up consecutive function calls by caching
       the result of calls with identical input.
     * [https://github.com/niksy/throttle-debounce]throttle-debounce -
       Throttle/debounce your functions.

Math

     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/is-number]is-number - Returns
       true if the value is a number.

Stream

     * [https://github.com/rvagg/through2]through2 - Tiny wrapper around
       Node streams2 Transform to avoid explicit subclassing noise.
     * [https://github.com/brycebaril/through2-filter]through2-filter - A
       through2 to create an Array.prototype.filter analog for streams.
     * [https://github.com/brycebaril/through2-map]through2-map - A
       through2 to create an Array.prototype.map analog for streams.
     * [https://github.com/brycebaril/node-stream-spigot]stream-spigot - A
       readable stream generator, useful for testing or converting simple
       functions into Readable streams.
     * [https://github.com/maxogden/concat-stream]concat-stream - writable
       stream that concatenates strings or data and calls a callback with
       the result.
     * [https://github.com/dominictarr/JSONStream]JSONStream - streaming
       JSON.parse and stringify
     * [https://github.com/RangerMauve/through2-map-promise]through2-map-p
       romise - A small promise-based wrapper for through2.
     * [https://github.com/mafintosh/pump]pump - pipe streams together and
       close all of them if one of them closes.
     * [https://github.com/dominictarr/split]split - Break up a stream and
       reassemble it so that each line is a chunk.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/is-stream]is-stream - Check if
       something is a Node.js stream.
     * [https://github.com/mcollina/syncthrough]syncthrough - Transform
       your data as it pass by, synchronously.

Promise

     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/pify]pify - Promisify a
       callback-style function.
     * [https://github.com/Siilwyn/promise-all-props]promise-all-props -
       Like Promise.all but for object properties.
     * [https://github.com/brummelte/sleep-promise]sleep-promise -
       Resolves a promise after a specified delay.
     * [https://github.com/then/is-promise]is-promise - Test whether an
       object looks like a promises-a+ promise.

File System

     * [https://github.com/isaacs/rimraf]rimraf - A deep deletion module
       for node (like rm -rf).
     * [https://github.com/substack/node-mkdirp]mkdirp - Recursively
       mkdir, like mkdir -p.
     * [https://github.com/rvagg/node-du]du - A simple JavaScript
       implementation of du -sb.
     * [https://github.com/Nijikokun/file-size]file-size - Lightweight
       filesize to human-readable / proportions w/o dependencies.
     * [https://github.com/raszi/node-tmp]tmp - Temporary file and
       directory creator for node.js.
     * [https://github.com/kevinbeaty/fs-promise]fs-promise - Node fs
       methods as Promise/A+ (optional fs-extra, graceful-fs).

Browser

     * [https://github.com/zenorocha/delegate]delegate - Lightweight event
       delegation.
     * [https://github.com/substack/insert-css]insert-css - Insert a
       string of css into the head
     * [https://github.com/crysalead-js/dom-element-value]dom-element-valu
       e - DOM element value getter/setter.
     * [https://github.com/bfred-it/image-promise]image-promise - Load one
       or more <img>s in a Promise.
     * [https://github.com/bfred-it/get-media-size]get-media-size - Get
       the original size of any img/video/svg/canvas tags or canvas
       context.
     * [https://github.com/bendrucker/document-ready]document-ready -
       Document ready listener for modern browsers.

Semver

     * [https://github.com/npm/node-semver]semver - The semantic version
       parser used by npm.
     * [https://github.com/eush77/semver-max]semver-max - Find maximum (or
       minimum) version according to semver.
     * [https://github.com/parro-it/semver-first-satisfied]semver-first-sa
       tisfied - Find minimum in an array of version that satisfies a
       semver range.

CLI

     * [https://github.com/isaacs/abbrev-js]abbrev - Calculate the set of
       unique abbreviations for a given set of strings.
     * [https://github.com/isaacs/node-glob]glob - Glob functionality for
       node.js.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/username]username - Get the
       username of the current user.
     * [https://github.com/substack/minimist]minimist - Parse argument
       options.
     * [https://github.com/steambap/png-to-ico]png-to-ico - Convert png to
       windows ico format.
     * [https://github.com/eush77/help-version]help-version - Easily
       handle --help and --version arguments in your CLI application

Module management

     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/pkg-conf]pkg-conf - Get namespaced
       config from the closest package.json.
     * [https://github.com/jonschlinkert/normalize-pkg]normalize-pkg -
       Normalize values in package.json to improve compatibility,
       programmatic readability and usefulness with third party libs.

Generators

     * [https://github.com/blakeembrey/is-generator]is-generator - Check
       whether a given value is a generator function.

Other

     * [https://github.com/kelektiv/node-uuid]uuid - Generate
       RFC-compliant UUIDs in JavaScript.
     * [https://github.com/broofa/node-mime]node-mime - Comprehensive MIME
       type mapping API based on mime-db module.
     * [https://github.com/fibo/not-defined]not-defined - Checks if foo is
       not defined, i.e. undefined, null, an empty string, array or
       object.
     * [https://github.com/parro-it/is-fqdn]is-fqdn - Check if a string
       represent a fully qualified domain name.

Related lists

   This section contains awesome lists that you may find useful if you use
   or write small NPM modules.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome-nodejs]awesome-nodejs - A
       curated list of delightful Node.js packages and resources.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome-npm]awesome-npm - Awesome
       npm resources and tips.

Small modules rockstars to follow

   These people are used to develop awesome NPM modules that follows the
   single responsibility philosophy. Follow them to discover new great
   modules:
   [https://github.com/sindresorhus]Sindre Sorhus
   [https://github.com/substack]James Halliday
   [https://github.com/eush77]Eugene Sharygin
   [https://github.com/isaacs]Isaac Z. Schlueter
